It was all glamour and glitz as the couple that won an all-expense paid-for wedding finally got married on Saturday.Daniel Makau and Beatrice Muthoni tied the knot during the beautiful ceremony held at the CITAM in Karen, followed by a stunning reception at the KCB Leadership Training Centre.The couple, who submitted their entry following the announcement of the Our Perfect Wedding competition in October last year, managed to clinch the top position after battling it out with 13 other couples. As a result, all the couple&rsquo;s expenses for the wedding were catered for by Maisha Magic East and Sarova Hotels, Resort and Game Lodges.Emcees for the grand ceremony were image consultant and motivational speaker Robert Burale and sensational comedian Dr Ofweneke, with Daddy Owen as the guest artiste.